Introduction and Objective
========================================================

### **Background**
***<p align=" justify">Carbon dioxide (CO<sub>2</sub>) emissions from the use of fossil fuels and the industrial processes are the main driving force of climate change. However, how this responsibility is divided across regions, nations, and people has long been a source of debate in international forums. Carbon Monitoring is an application providing the regularly updated, science-based estimates of CO<sub>2</sub> emissions.</p>

### **Objective**
<p align=" justify">To investigate the level of carbon emission globally and monitor various sources of carbon emissions which contribute to climate change.</p>


***
### **Questions**

- <p align=" justify">How has carbon emission changed over the year?</p>
- <p align=" justify">What is the global carbon emission per day per country per capita?</p>
- <p align=" justify">Which country has the highest & lowest carbon emission?</p>
- <p align=" justify">What are the sources of carbon emission for respective country?</p>
- <p align=" justify">How does carbon emission correlate with global temperature and global mean sea level?</p>

### **Type of Data Product**
Data as a Service


