<div class='left' style='float:left;width:40%'>
<hgroup>
    Features of Carbon Monitoring App:
</hgroup>


<ul type=&#8221;circle&#8221;>		
<li><p align="justify", style="font-size:20px;"><b>Global CO<sub>2</sub> :</b> This tab allows users to have an overview of CO<sub>2</sub> emission of individual countries in a world map view, together with their historical trend and changes.</p></li>
<li><p align="justify", style="font-size:20px;"><b>Source of Emission :</b> The tab illustrates the proportion and historical sources of emission of CO<sub>2</sub>, such as from oil, coal, cement, gas etc., for each country, based on users selection.</p></li>
<li><p align="justify", style="font-size:20px;"><b>Atmospheric CO<sub>2</sub> :</b>The tab demonstrates the positive relationship between CO<sub>2</sub> Emission, CO<sub>2</sub> level in atmosphere, and the mean sea level.</p></li>
<li><p align="justify", style="font-size:20px;"><b>Country Ranking :</b> The tab shows the top countries with the highest CO<sub>2</sub> emission indices, including CO<sub>2</sub> Production, CO<sub>2</sub> Production Per Capita, and Cumulative CO<sub>2</sub> Production.</p></li>
<li><p align="justify", style="font-size:20px;"><b>User Guide :</b>The tab demonstrates how to use the developed CO<sub>2</sub> Tracker Shiny App together with its functions.</p></li>
<li><p align="justify", style="font-size:20px;"><b>Data :</b> The tab allows users to download the dependency datasets used by CO<sub>2</sub> Tracker in CSV format.</p></li>
</UL>
</div>



